ter20190409\">{{cite web |last1=Lewis |first1=Hilary |title=Peabody Awards: ''Killing Eve,'' ''Pose,'' ''The Good Place'' Among Nominees |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/peabody-award-nominations-2019-list-full-1194383/item/news-1194408 |publisher=Hollywood Reporter |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190410171907/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/peabody-award-nominations-2019-list-full-1194383/item/news-1194408 |archivedate=10 April 2019 |date=9 April 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"BroadwayWorld20190418\">{{cite news |author1=TV News Desk |title=''Barry,'' ''Killing Eve'' Among 2019 Peabody Award Winners |url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwtv/article/BARRY-KILLING-EVE-Among-2019-Peabody-Award-Winners-20190418 |work=Broadway World |date=18 April 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190418182558/https://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwtv/article/BARRY-KILLING-EVE-Among-2019-Peabody-Award-Winners-20190418 |archivedate=18 April 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | [[71st Primetime Creative Arts Emmy Awards|Primetime Creative Arts Emmy Awards]]\n| [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Casting for a Drama Series|Outstanding Casting for a Drama Series]]\n| data-sort-value=\"Crowley, Suzanne and Gilly Poole\" | Suzanne Crowley and Gilly Poole\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"9\" style=\"text-align: center;\" | <ref name=ATAS_20190716>{{cite web |title=2019 Primetime Emmy \u00ae Awards / Nomination Press Release |url=https://www.emmys.com/sites/default/files/Downloads/71st-nominations-list-v1.pdf |website=emmys.com |publisher=Academy of Television Arts & Sciences |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190716222258/https://www.emmys.com/sites/default/files/Downloads/71st-nominations-list-v1.pdf |archivedate=16 July 2019 |date=16 July 2019 |url-status=dead }}</ref><!-- (earlier, incomplete refs) <ref name=LATimes_20190716>{{cite news |title=2019 Emmy nominations: Complete list |url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment-arts/tv/story/2019-07-16/emmy-nominations-2019-complete-list-of-nominees |work=Los Angeles Times |date=16 July 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190716163730/https://www.latimes.com/entertainment-arts/tv/story/2019-07-16/emmy-nominations-2019-complete-list-of-nominees |archivedate=16 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=NYTimes_20190716>{{cite news |last1=Aridi |first1=Sara |title=Here's a List of the 2019 Emmy Nominations |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/07/16/arts/television/emmy-nominations-list.html |work=The New York Times |date=16 July 2019}}</ref> --><ref name=Vox_20190922>{{cite web |last1=Abad-Santos |first1=Alex |title=Emmys 2019 winners: the complete list |url=https://www.vox.com/2019/9/22/20878907/2019-emmys-winners-full-list-game-of-thrones-fleabag |website=Vox (website) |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190923185918/https://www.vox.com/2019/9/22/20878907/2019-emmys-winners-full-list-game-of-thrones-fleabag |archivedate=23 September 2019 |date=22 September 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Production Design for a Narrative Contemporary Program (One Hour or More)|Outstanding Production Design for a Narrative Contemporary Program (One Hour or More)]]\n| data-sort-value=\"Dorman, Laurence, Beckie Harvey and Linda Wilson\" | Laurence Dorman, Beckie Harvey and Linda Wilson (for \"The Hungry Caterpillar\")\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Single-Camera Picture Editing for a Drama Series|Outstanding Single-Camera Picture Editing for a Drama Series]]\n| data-sort-value=\"Crinnion, Dan\" | Dan Crinnion (for \"Desperate Times\")\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\" |[[71st Primetime Emmy Awards|Primetime Emmy Awards]]\n|[[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Directing for a Drama Series|Outstanding Directing for a Drama Series]]\n| data-sort-value=\"Br\u00fclmann, Lisa\" |Lisa Br\u00fchlmann (for \"Desperate Times\")\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|[[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Dram