 Emmy Awards]]\n|[[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Directing for a Drama Series|Outstanding Directing for a Drama Series]]\n| data-sort-value=\"Br\u00fclmann, Lisa\" |Lisa Br\u00fchlmann (for \"Desperate Times\")\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|[[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Drama Series|Outstanding Drama Series]]\n| data-sort-value=\"Gentle, Sally Woodward, Lee Morris\" | Sally Woodward Gentle, Lee Morris, Phoebe Waller-Bridge, Emerald Fennell, Gina Mingacci, Damon Thomas, Francesca Gardiner, Sandra Oh, Elinor Day, Morenike Williams and Andy Noble\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | Outstanding Lead Actress in a Drama Series\n| data-sort-value=\"Comer, Jodie\" | Jodie Comer (for \"I Hope You Like Missionary!\")\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| data-sort-value=\"Oh, Sandra\" | Sandra Oh (for \"You're Mine\")\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Supporting Actress in a Drama Series|Outstanding Supporting Actress in a Drama Series]] \n| data-sort-value=\"Shaw, Fiona\" | Fiona Shaw (for \"Nice and Neat\")\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Outstanding Writing for a Drama Series\n| data-sort-value=\"Fennell, Emerald (Nice and Neat)\" | Emerald Fennell (for \"Nice and Neat\")\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[23rd Satellite Awards|Satellite Awards]]\n| [[Satellite Award for Best Actress \u2013 Television Series Drama|Best Actress in a Drama / Genre Series]]\n| data-sort-value=\"Oh, Sandra\" | Sandra Oh\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" |<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pressacademy.com/2018-nominees/ |title=2018 Nominees |work=International Press Academy |date=28 November 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181129183902/http://www.pressacademy.com/2018-nominees/ |archivedate=29 November 2018 |url-status=dead |access-date=2 December 2018 }}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[45th Saturn Awards|Saturn Awards]]\n| Best Action-Thriller Television Series\n| ''Killing Eve''\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align: center;\" |<ref>{{cite web |last1=Mancuso |first1=Vinnie |title='Avengers: Endgame', 'Game of Thrones' Lead the 2019 Saturn Awards Nominations |url=http://collider.com/saturn-awards-nominations-2019/ |website=Collider |accessdate=17 July 2019 |date=16 July 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| Best Actress in a Television Series\n| data-sort-value=\"Oh, Sandra\" | Sandra Oh\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[25th Screen Actors Guild Awards|Screen Actors Guild Awards]]\n| [[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by a Female Actor in a Drama Series|Outstanding Performance by a Female Actor in a Drama Series]]\n| data-sort-value=\"Oh, Sandra\" | Sandra Oh\n| {{won}}\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | <ref name=\"CNN20181212\">{{cite web |last1=France |first1=Lisa Respers France |title=SAG Awards 2019: See if your faves got nominated |url=https://www.cnn.com/2018/12/12/entertainment/sag-awards-2019/index.html |work=CNN |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181212163711/https://www.cnn.com/2018/12/12/entertainment/sag-awards-2019/index.html |archivedate=12 December 2018 |date=12 December 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=SAGrecipients_2019>{{cite web |title=The 25th Annual Screen Actors Guild Awards / Nominees and Recipients / Television |url=https://www.sagawards.org/nominees/nominees-and-recipients/25th-annual-screen-actors-guild-awards |website=SAGawards.com |publisher=(Screen Actors Guild) |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190910151451/https://www.sagawards.org/nominees/nominees-and-recipients/25th-annual-screen-actors-guild-awards |archivedate=10 September 2019 |date=January 2019 |url-status=live }} (Click on \"Television\" tab.)</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[35th TCA Awards|Television Critics Association Awards]]\n| Individual Achievement in Drama\n| data-sort-value=\"Comer, Jodie\" | Jodie Comer\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align: center;\" | <ref name=\"Vulture_20190619\">{{cite news |last1=McHenry |first1=Jackson |title=''Pose'' and ''Russian Doll'' Lead the TV Critics Association Award Nominations |url=https://www.vulture.com/2019/06/pose-and-russian-doll-lead-the-tca-award-nominations-2019.html |work=Vulture ([[New York (magazine)|New York magazine]]) |date=19 June 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190619172706/https://www.vulture.com/2019/06/pose-and-russian-doll-lead-the-tca-award-nominations-2019.html |archivedate=19 June 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n|-\n| Outstanding Achievement in Drama\n|''Killing Eve''\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"9\" | 2020\n| [[Costume Designers Guild Awards 2019|Costume Designers Guild Awards]]\n| [[Costume Designers Guild Award for Best Costume Design \u2013 Contemporary TV Series|Excellence in Contemporary Television]]\n| data-sort-value=\"Mitchell, Charlotte\" | Charlotte Mitchell (for \"Desperate Times\") \n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" |<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/2020-costume-designers-guild-awards-full-list-nominations-1259668 |title=Costume Designers Guild Awards: 'Hustlers,' 'Rocketman' Among Nominees |website=The Hollywood Reporter |first=Lindsay |last=Weinberg |date=10 December 2019 |accessdate=11 January 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[10th Critics' Choice Television Awards|Critics Choice Awards]] \n| Best Actress in a Drama Series\n| data-sort-value=\"Comer, Jodie\" | Jodie Comer\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | <ref name=HollywoodRep_20191208>{{cite news |author1=THR Staff |title=Critics' Choice Awards: 'The Irishman' Leads With 14 Nominations |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/2020-critics-choice-awards-nominations-list-full-1260595/item/2020-critics-choice-awards-best-actress-a-drama-series-1260624 |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=8 December 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191209051649/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/2020-critics-choice-awards-nominations-list-full-1260595/item/2020-critics-choice-awards-best-actress-a-drama-series-1260624 |archivedate=9 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[31st GLAAD Media Awards|GLAAD Media A