{"title_page": "Dylan O'Brien", "text_new": "{{short description|American actor}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name         = Dylan O'Brien\n| image        = Dylan O'Brien by Gage Skidmore 2.jpg\n| caption      = O'Brien at the 2017 [[San Diego Comic-Con]]\n| birth_date   = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1991|8|26}}\n| birth_place  = [[New York City]], [[New York (state)|New York]], United States\n| education    = [[Mira Costa High School]]\n| occupation   = Actor\n| years active = 2011{{endash}}present\n| home_town    = [[Springfield Township, Union County, New Jersey|Springfield Township, New Jersey]], U.S.\n}}\n'''Dylan O'Brien''' (born August 26, 1991) is an American actor. He is known for his lead role as Thomas in the ''[[Maze Runner (film series)|Maze Runner]]'' dystopian science fiction trilogy and for his role as [[List of Teen Wolf characters#Main characters|Stiles Stilinski]] in the [[MTV]] television series ''[[Teen Wolf (2011 TV series)|Teen Wolf]]''. O'Brien's other work includes starring roles in films such as ''[[The First Time (2012 film)|The First Time]]'' and ''[[American Assassin]]'' and supporting roles in ''[[The Internship]]'' and ''[[Deepwater Horizon (film)|Deepwater Horizon]]''.\n\n==Early life==\nO'Brien was born in [[New York City]], the son of Lisa (n\u00e9e Rhodes), a former actress who also ran an acting school, and Patrick O'Brien, a camera operator.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.skidmore.edu/scope/fall2009/classnotes/1986.htm |title=Skidmore Scope Fall 2009 |last=Stuzin |first=Anne Chorske |website=Skidmore Scope |accessdate=March 23, 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"Real\">{{cite web |url=http://www.teentelevision.com/2011/06/27/teen-wolfs-dylan-o-brien-in-real-life-i-m-the-were |title=Teen Wolf's Dylan O'Brien 'In real life, I'm the werewolf.' |last=Barker |first=Lynn |website=Teen Television |date=July 27, 2011 |accessdate=July 27, 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110802074222/http://www.teentelevision.com/2011/06/27/teen-wolfs-dylan-o-brien-in-real-life-i-m-the-were |archivedate=August 2, 2011}}</ref> He grew up in [[Springfield Township, Union County, New Jersey|Springfield Township, New Jersey]], until the age of twelve with his lifelong friend Mia Kadyan, when he and his family moved to [[Hermosa Beach, California]].<ref>[http://dylanobrien.org/about/biography/ \"Biography\"]. Dylan O'Brien Online. Retrieved February 6, 2017.</ref><ref>Hixon, Michael (April 22, 2014). [http://tbrnews.com/lifestyle/former-hermosa-beach-resident-stars-in-potential-blockbuster-dylan-o/article_fba30032-ca74-11e3-b9ef-0019bb2963f4.html \"Former Hermosa Beach resident stars in potential blockbuster: Dylan O'Brien got his break on MTV's 'Teen Wolf' but will star in the feature film 'The Maze Runner' in September\"]. ''[[The Beach Reporter]]''.</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.popentertainment.com/dylanobrien.htm |title=Dylan O'Brien interview about 'The First Time' and 'Teen Wolf.' |last=Jacobs |first=Jay S. |date=October 19, 2012 |website=PopEntertainment.com |accessdate=September 4, 2013}}</ref> His father is of [[Irish people|Irish]] descent, and his mother is of Italian, English and Spanish ancestry.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.asiaone.com/News/Latest%2BNews/Showbiz/Story/A1Story20120601-349879.html |title=Sidekick supreme |last=Johnson |first=Jason |website=[[AsiaOne]] |date=June 4, 2012 |accessdate=June 4, 2012}}</ref> After graduating from [[Mira Costa High School]] in 2009, he considered pursuing [[sports broadcasting]] and possibly working for the [[New York Mets]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.teenvogue.com/entertainment/movies/2014-08/dylan-obrien-maze-runner/?slide=1 |title=Up Close and Personal with Dylan O'Brien: The 'Maze Runner' Star Talks Movies, Making It, and More |last=Mathews |first=Dana |date=2013 |newspaper=[[Teen Vogue]] |accessdate=September 8, 2014}}</ref> At 14, O'Brien began posting original videos onto his [[YouTube]] channel. With the videos developing, a local producer and director approached him about doing work for a web series while in his senior year of high school.<ref name=\"Real\" /> While working on the webseries, O'Brien met an actor who connected him with a manager. He had planned to attend [[Syracuse University]]<ref>Stark, Stephanie (July 6, 2011). [https://gotham-magazine.com/one-to-watch-teen-wolfs-dylan-obrien \"One to Watch: ''Teen Wolf''{{'}}s Dylan O'Brien\"]. ''[[Gotham (magazine)|Gotham]]''.</ref> as a sports broadcasting major, but decided to pursue an acting career instead.<ref>Callaway, Tyler (October 10, 2015). [https://moviepilot.com/posts/2925590 \"Dylan O'Brien Is on the Rise in Hollywood. Here's Why He Will Be the Next Big Star\"]. [[Moviepilot]]. October 10, 2015.</ref>\n\n==Career==\nBefore beginning his career in acting, O'Brien produced, directed and starred in a number of comedic short films which he released through his personal YouTube channel.<ref>{{cite av media |last=O'Brien |first=Dylan |url=https://www.youtube.com/user/moviekidd826 |title=Dis Be My Channel |via=[[YouTube]] |accessdate=February 6, 2017}}</ref> He was also the drummer for the independent rock band Slow Kids at Play.<ref>Hixon, Michael (October 15, 2013). [http://tbrnews.com/lifestyle/back-at-play-local-band-slow-kids-at-play-gets/article_246afc7c-35ce-11e3-936f-0019bb2963f4.html \"Back at 'Play': Local band Slow Kids at Play gets new members and outlook. They will perform at Saint Rocke on Saturday\"]. ''The Beach Reporter''.</ref>\n\nHe went through several auditions before getting one of the main roles in MTV's ''[[Teen Wolf (2011 TV series)|Teen Wolf]]'', a series loosely based on the 1985 film of the [[Teen Wolf|same name]]. He had been intended to play Scott, but after reading the script, O'Brien wanted to audition for the part of Stiles instead.<ref>{{cite web |last=Radish |first=Christina |url=http://collider.com/dylan-obrien-interview-teen-wolf/ |title=Dylan O'Brien Interview TEEN WOLF |website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]] |date=July 8, 2011}}</ref> After four auditions, he was cast.<ref name=\"Real\" /> In 2010, he began playing Stiles in the series.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://thefutoncritic.com/news/2010/08/06/mtv-builds-slate-of-scripted-programming-with-2011-premieres-of-original-series-teen-wolf-and-skins-36898/20100806mtv01/ |title=Breaking News \u2013 MTV Builds Slate of Scripted Programming with 2011 Premieres of Original Series 'Teen Wolf' and 'Skins' |work=[[The Futon Critic]] |date=August 6, 2010}}</ref>\n\nIn 2011, O'Brien was introduced to audiences in the entirely improvised independent comedy film ''[[High Road (film)|High Road]]''. The following year, he starred opposite [[Britt Robertson]] in the romantic comedy ''[[The First Time (2012 film)|The First Time]]''.<!--- keep Robertson mention as they started long term relationship after --->\n\nIn 2013, O'Brien co-starred in the comedy film ''[[The Internship]]''. That same year, O'Brien filmed ''[[The Maze Runner (film)|The Maze Runner]]'' which began filming in summer 2013, while he was on hiatus from ''Teen Wolf''.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://twitter.com/dylanobrien/status/324999088305217536 |title=SO excited to join the cast of #MazeRunner @wesball @jamesdashner thank you for including me in this insanely awesome project. Can't wait!! |last=O'Brien |first=Dylan |date=April 19, 2013 |website=[[Twitter]] |accessdate=May 20, 2013}}</ref> He played Thomas, the lead role. [[Yahoo! Movies]] named O'Brien as one of the 15 Breakout Stars to Watch for in 2014.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://movies.yahoo.com/blogs/yahoo-movies/15-breakout-stars-watch-2014-213625337.html |title=15 Breakout Stars to Watch for in 2014 |last=Warner |first=Kara |date=January 3, 2014 |website=[[Yahoo! Movies]] |accessdate=September 6, 2014}}</ref> He reprised the role of Thomas in ''[[Maze Runner: The Scorch Trials]]'', released in September 18, 2015.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/jarettwieselman/a-maze-runner-sequel-is-already-in-pre-production |title=A \"Maze Runner\" Sequel Is Already in Pre-Production |first=Jarett |last=Wieselman |date=September 4, 2014 |accessdate=September 6, 2014 |work=[[BuzzFeed]]}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2016, O'Brien was seriously injured on set while filming a stunt for ''[[Maze Runner: The Death Cure]]''. O'Brien was in a harness on top of a moving vehicle when he was pulled off the vehicle unexpectedly and hit by another vehicle. His injuries included facial fractures, a concussion, and brain trauma.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.vulture.com/2017/09/dylan-obrien-is-back-from-the-brink.html |title=Dylan O'Brien Is Ready to Talk About That Accident |first=Kyle |last=Buchanan |date=September 7, 2017 |website=Vulture}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://deadline.com/2016/03/dylan-obrien-hurt-maze-runner-death-trials-production-stopped-fox-1201722730/ |title='Maze Runner: Death Cure' Production Shut Down After Dylan O'Brien Injured On Set |last=Hipes |first=Patrick |last2=Busch |first2=Anita |website=Deadline Hollywood |date=April 29, 2016}}</ref> O'Brien later stated that the accident \"'broke most of the right side'\" of his face; he underwent reconstructive facial surgery.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.sltrib.com/artsliving/movies/2017/09/14/after-on-set-accident-left-him-with-a-severe-head-injury-heartthrob-dylan-obrien-bounces-back-in-american-assassin/ |title=After on-set accident left him with a severe head injury, heartthrob Dylan O'Brien bounces back in 'American Assassin' |website=The Salt Lake Tribune}}</ref> After months of recovery, O'Brien eventually began filming other projects, and his March 2017 return to ''The Death Cure'' set marked his complete return to health.<ref name=\"DeadlineHollywood\">{{cite web |url=http://deadline.com/2016/08/maze-runner-the-death-cure-will-start-production-in-feb-1201810382/ |title='The Maze Runner: The Death Cure' Will Restart Production In February |website=Deadline Hollywood |first=Anita |last=Busch |date=August 29, 2016 |accessdate=August 30, 2016}}</ref> The film premiered on January 26, 2018.<ref name=\"DeadlineHollywood\" /><ref name=\"Deadline\">{{cite web |url=http://deadline.com/2017/04/deadpool-2-new-mutants-dark-phoenix-bohemian-rhapsody-steven-spielberg-pentagon-papers-1202075186/ |title='Deadpool 2', 'New Mutants' & 'Dark Phoenix' Find 2018 Dates Among Fox's Slew Of Release Changes & Additions |first=Anthony |last=D'Alessandro |date=April 22, 2017 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]}}</ref><ref name=\"Variety\">{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2017/film/awards/steven-spielberg-pentagon-papers-movie-the-post-1202539636/ |title=Steven Spielberg's Pentagon Papers Movie Re-Titled 'The Post' |date=August 25, 2017 |first=McNary |last=Dave |work=Variety |accessdate=August 26, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, he appeared in the disaster thriller-drama ''[[Deepwater Horizon (film)|Deepwater Horizon]]'', based on the 2010 [[Deepwater Horizon explosion]]. He starred in 2017's ''[[American Assassin]]'', an action-thriller in which he played the titular character [[Mitch Rapp]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://deadline.com/2016/05/dylan-obrien-american-assassin-maze-runner-vince-flynn-cbs-films-lionsgate-1201752315// |title='Maze Runner's Dylan O'Brien In Talks To Play Mitch Rapp In Vince Flynn Spy Novel Adaptation 'American Assassin' |first=Mike |last=Fleming Jr |date=May 10, 2016 |website=Deadline Hollywood}}</ref><ref>Wein, Dick (July 29, 2016). [https://www.cbscorporation.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/7.29.16.pdf \"CBS Continues to Chart the Future\"]. ''Update'', Vol. 18, No. 878, [[CBS Corporation]]. p. 11.</ref> and voiced the [[Computer-generated imagery|CGI]] title character in the ''[[Transformers]]'' spin-off film ''[[Bumblebee (film)|Bumblebee]]'' in 2018.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://uk.ign.com/articles/2018/12/03/transformers-bumblebee-movie-voice-actor-dylan-obrien |title=Bumblebee Voice Actor Revealed |last=Vejvoda |first=Jim |website=IGN |date=3 Dec 2018 |accessdate=3 Dec 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, O'Brien guest-starred in the comedic sci-fi anthology series ''[[Weird City (TV series)|Weird City]]''.<ref name=\"Weird_City\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/07/weird-city-sara-gilbert-dylan-obrien-rosario-dawson-laverne-cox-among-guests-stars-set-for-jordan-peele-sci-fi-anthology-on-youtube-1202435233/ |title='Weird City': Sara Gilbert, Dylan O'Brien, Laverne Cox Among Guest Stars Set For Jordan Peele Sci-Fi Anthology On YouTube |last=Petski |first=Denise |date=27 Jul 2018 |website=Deadline |accessdate=3 Aug 2018}}</ref> Upcoming releases include the titular role in the mystery thriller ''[[The Education of Fredrick Fitzell]]'', filmed in 2018,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://deadline.com/2018/05/the-maze-runner-star-dylan-obrien-it-follows-star-maika-monroe-set-for-mystery-thriller-fitzell-1202382638/ |title=Dylan O'Brien & Maika Monroe To Star In Thriller 'The Education Of Fredrick Fitzell' |last=Wiseman |first=Andreas |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=May 4, 2018 |accessdate=May 6, 2018}}</ref> and the post-apocalyptic road trip film ''Monster Problems'', in which he will star alongside [[Michael Rooker]] and [[Ariana Greenblatt]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/03/ariana-greenblatt-avengers-infinity-war-actress-joins-dylan-obrien-monster-problems-1202580776/ |title=Ariana Greenblatt Joins Dylan O'Brien In Paramount Players' 'Monster Problems' |last=D'Alessandro |first=Anthony |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=March 22, 2019 |accessdate=March 28, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n[[Image:Dylan O'Brien 2014 Comic Con (cropped).jpg|thumb|200px|O'Brien at ComicCon, 2014]]\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| rowspan=2|2011\n| ''Charlie Brown: Blockhead's Revenge''\n| [[Charlie Brown]]\n| Short film<ref>{{cite web |title=Charlie Brown: Blockhead's Revenge |url=http://www.funnyordie.com/videos/fec6d23f5c/charlie-brown-blockheads-revenge |work=Funny or Die |date=October 27, 2011 |accessdate=June 6, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[High Road (film)|High Road]]''\n| Jimmy\n|\n|-\n| 2012\n| data-sort-value=\"First Time, The\" | ''[[The First Time (2012 film)|The First Time]]''\n| Dave Hodgman\n| \n|-\n| 2013\n| data-sort-value=\"Internship, The\" | ''[[The Internship]]''\n| Stuart Twombly\n| \n|-\n| 2014\n| data-sort-value=\"Maze Runner, The\" | ''[[The Maze Runner (film)|The Maze Runner]]''\n|Thomas\n| \n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[Maze Runner: The Scorch Trials]]''\n|Thomas\n|\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Deepwater Horizon (film)|Deepwater Horizon]]''\n| Caleb Holloway\n|\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[American Assassin]]''\n| [[Mitch Rapp]]\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2018\n|''[[Bumblebee (film)|Bumblebee]]''\n|[[Bumblebee (Transformers)|Bumblebee]] (voice)\n| \n|-\n| ''[[Maze Runner: The Death Cure]]''\n| Thomas\n|\n|-\n| 2020\n|''[[Infinite (film)|Infinite]]''\n|\n| Post-production\n|-\n| 2020\n| data-sort-value=\"Education of Fredrick Fitzell, The\" | ''[[The Education of Fredrick Fitzell]]''\n| Fredrick Fitzell\n| Completed\n|-\n| 2021<ref>{{cite web |title=Controversial Gang Saga ''Blue Story'' Release Date Moved By Paramount |url=https://deadline.com/2020/02/blue-story-gang-saga-film-release-date-moved-by-paramount-1202860719/ |date=February 14, 2020 |accessdate=February 14, 2020}}</ref>\n|''[[Monster Problems]]''\n| Joel Dawson\n| Post-production\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2011\u20132017\n| ''[[Teen Wolf (2011 TV series)|Teen Wolf]]''\n| [[List of Teen Wolf characters#Stiles Stilinski|Stiles Stilinski]]\n| Main role\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''First Dates with Toby Harris''\n| Peter\n| Web series short; episode: \"Roommates\"<ref>{{cite web |title=First Dates with Toby Harris |url=https://vimeopro.com/elliotdickerhoof/first-dates-with-toby-harris/video/106136712 |work=Vimeo Pro |accessdate=June 6, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2013\n